1.Introduction
 .Wrie clean and modular code.
 .Improve code effciency
 .Add effective documentation
 .Use version control
------------------------------
2.Clean and Modular Code
 .CLEAN: readable, simple, and concise.
 .MODULAR: logically broken up into functions and modules.
 .MODULE: a file. Modules allow code to be reused by encapsulating them into files that can be imported into other files.
------------------------------
3.Refactoring Code
 .Restructuring code t0 improve internal structure without changing external functionality.
 -Why refactor
  .reduce workload long run
  .easy to maintain code
  .reuse more of your code
  .become a better developer.
------------------------------
4.Writing clean code
 .Be descriptive and imply type
 .Be consistent but clearly differentiate
 .Avoid abbreviations and especially single letters
 .Long names != descriptive names 
 .Use whitespace properly
--------------------------------
	


		
